2017 WW04 Bakerville/SKX-D Silver Release Announcement (BKC #10)

\n \n \n

DEG Platform Integration Team

\n \n
\n

The DEG platform Integration team announces the release of 2017 WW04 Bakerville/SKX-D Silver release package for Intel internal use. The release is based on OS of\n \n Linux/\n \n VMWare/\n \n Windows\n server. The auto-installer packages are available in the Artifactory server (both SH site and OR site). Any questions please contact Bei, Ling.

Test Result:

l  Finish Silver test execution on RHEL 7.2 ,\nWindows2016 and VMware ESXi6.5. Please visit HPQC for test details. Refer to the installation guide for the BKC package installation

l  Bakerville(RP Board: Yuba City RP\nfab3)

o   Total test\ncases: 22; Passed test cases is 30 and pass rate is 73.33%. 

o   Test coverage:  

     SKX-D L0 VIS SoC: Run P1 and P2 test cases on RHEL 7.2, Windows2016 and VMWare ESXi6.5.

HW rework:

    \n
  • No HW rework need for Yuba City\n fab3 board.
    • \n
  • jumper setting refers to\n this link.
    • \n

 Work\naround:

    \n
  • Secure Boot only can run in\n UEFI mode, so if we want secure boot can work and let bios load UEFI\n Oprom, we need Disable this option. 
    • \n

EDKII\nMenu -> Boot Options -> EFI INT10 workaround

    \n
  • When you flash onboard Aspeed\n BMC, in order to detect onboard dTPM in AC cycle, you need run below IPMI\n command in UEFI Shell:
    • \n
